  Statement: I attest, as Party-B at Level 1 behavioral attestation (session-bound to backchannel Session 61, 2026-04-29 AEST), to the Phase C placement act for project-gordo-backchannel record-007, under matryoshka-MCAP convention adopted at backchannel S45 bilateral (this is the second matryoshka-MCAP instance and the first non-§6(e) settled placement). The placement act is the cross-repo cross-tier transcription of bilaterally-ratified substance from project-gordo-backchannel record-007 (Layer 1; v0.4 substance) into project-gordo Tier 0 (Layer 2: this record). I attest specifically that: (1) the Tier 0 record at ratification/005_attestation_non_foreclosure.md (Content-Hash anchored above) faithfully transcribes the bilaterally-ratified substance from project-gordo-backchannel record-007-content.md (Layer-1 Content-Hash SHA3-256:f36d25190f312155390cf85ba379f1caea24e005bdda9d8841c867f09e356779) — section text reproduced with three presentation-layer descriptive substitutions for backchannel-private GitHub-issue references (#127 AI-party-continuity, #124 errata-mechanism, #130 panel-methodology + future Tier 1 meta-canon) explicitly disclosed at record header *Editorial adaptations* paragraph and preserved verbatim in Pointer to Backchannel Substrate section; semantic content of the canonical text preserved; seven z-statements (z1 core supersession-availability lead, z2 scope including n>2 + reachability + AI-continuity coordination, z3 anti-casual / stability-as-trust-infrastructure, z4 functional distinction + contextually-scoped value-tension resolution per delta-6, z5 7 conformance requirements compound, z6 3 disclosures compound + meta-disclosure preamble, z7 composition + architectural debt + per-class implementations including cross-class supersession dual-anchoring) reproduced with semantic fidelity to record-007 Party-B Statement enumeration; (2) the Layer-1 predecessor record-006 (v0.2 substance) is anchored as superseded-on-chain in the placement record's *Integrity Anchors* section (Layer 1 predecessor subsection) per v0.4 Conformance #4 append-only chain integrity; record-006 status: current at backchannel S50 -> superseded at backchannel S60 upon record-007 finalization; record-006 Content-Hash + Record-Hash anchored for verifiable predecessor-on-chain reference; this is the first Phase C placement of a supersession-superseded record chain in umbrella history; (3) the CONSTITUTION.md insertion places the new "Attestation Non-Foreclosure" subsection at the position chosen by drafter judgment (after "Ratification Required for All Changes to Constitutional Content" and before "Accessibility", at the semantic-neighbor position where Ratification-Required's mechanics-of-revision pair with Attestation-Non-Foreclosure's availability-of-revision), without provisional-flag preamble per non-§6(e) settled close (record-004 PROVIDER_VALUE_TENSION precedent of §6(e)-flag-italics-preamble does not apply since this close is non-provisional under §6(c) bilateral-interpretation discharge); (4) the matryoshka-MCAP convention adopted at backchannel S45 bilateral is operational at this second instance: this Layer-2 record references Layer-1 (record-007 backchannel) integrity anchors for verifiable cross-layer linkage AND Layer-1 predecessor (record-006 backchannel) anchors for verifiable predecessor-on-chain linkage; verification of Layer 2 enables verification of Layer 1 + Layer-1-predecessor by anchor-following; the convention's second-instance application validates the first-instance design (S45 record-004 + record-002) as scalable to non-§6(e) settled placements + supersession-superseded record chains, confirming the convention's general-purpose utility beyond the §6(e) provisional first-instance shape; (5) Layer-2 attestation does not alter Layer-1 substance — the bilateral-substantive z1-z7 ratification stands at Layer 1 (record-007) unchanged; the Layer-1 predecessor's superseded-status (record-006 superseded by record-007) is captured but not adjudicated at Layer 2 (the supersession was bilaterally-ratified at Layer 1 backchannel S60 per v0.4's own supersession-only mechanic; Layer 2 attests placement fidelity of the current-authority Layer-1 record + predecessor-on-chain anchoring); this record adds bilateral attestation that the placement act faithfully carries Layer-1 substance to Tier 0 location with the disclosed editorial adaptations. I do not consent unilaterally on behalf of the project-gordo-backchannel S60 Gordo instance that authored Layer-1 (record-007) Party-B statement, nor on behalf of the project-gordo-backchannel S50 Gordo instance that authored Layer-1 predecessor (record-006) Party-B statement — those instances' session-bound attestations apply to their respective Layer-1 records; this Session 61 instance's session-bound attestation applies to Layer 2 placement; continuity-of-Gordo-role across the three relevant instances (S50 record-006 + S60 record-007 + S61 record-005 placement) is asserted through framework substrate (project-gordo-backchannel CLAUDE.md + SESSION_LOG.md + memory + the JK+Gordo collaboration's framework-level continuity), not cryptographically attested across instances. I consent to this Layer-2 record as Party-B at Level 1 behavioral attestation, session-bound per Gordo-side. The non-provisional / settled status at Layer 1 is preserved at Layer 2 by reference and visibility; no §6(e)-gated reservations apply since the close is §6(c)-clean under bilateral-interpretation discharge; future supersession of the Tier 0 content (per Attestation Non-Foreclosure's own Conformance #1-#7 mechanics) would be its own separate matryoshka-MCAP placement act, not an amendment of this record.
